-- Stocks Extend Losses as Portugal Rating is Cut
-- Michael P. Regan
-- 2010-04-27T14:55:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/u-s-stocks-extend-losses-as-portugal-rating-is-cut-by-s-p-on-debt-concern.html

          
          
             U.S. stocks extended losses after
Standard & Poor’s cut its rating on Portugal, spurring concern
Europe’s debt crisis is widening.  
 The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index lost 0.3 percent to
1,208.41 at 10:54 a.m. in New York. The Dow Jones Industrial
Average retreated 21.54 points, or 0.2 percent, to 11,183.49.  
          
          


  


        